{
  "texts": [
    "and note that D ii ′ captures the difference in empirical average model behavior between f i and f i ′ with respect to {q 1,.",
    ", q m } and g. With the form described by Eq.",
    "(1), D is a rescaled Euclidean distance matrix.",
    "Hence, multidimensional scaling (MDS) of D yields ddimensional Euclidean representations of the matrices Xi (and thereby of the models f i) with respect to {q 1,.",
    ", q m } and g (Torgerson, 1952)."
  ]
}